user_request:
Create a complete Todo List component using Chakra UI.
Use useState for internal state: todos (empty array) and inputValue (empty string).
Include an Input and 'Add' Button with necessary handlers (handleInputChange, handleAddTodo).
Render the list using a .map() over the todos state, creating an HStack for each todo item directly inside the main VStack (do not use List or ListItem).
Inside each item's HStack:
Render a self-closing <Checkbox> with isChecked and onChange props.
Render a separate, sibling <Text> component displaying the todo.text. Apply line-through style if todo.completed is true.
Render an <IconButton> with aria-label='Delete todo', size='sm', colorPalette='red', and an onClick handler. Crucially, render the text 'X' as a direct child of this IconButton, like <IconButton ... >X</IconButton>. Do NOT use the icon prop.
Define all necessary handlers (handleInputChange, handleAddTodo, handleToggleComplete, handleDeleteTodo) inside the component body.
